sections.History:
===[[Season 1]]===
[[File:Arya chasing cat Episode 105.jpg|thumb|Arya chases a cat through the Red Keep]]
[[File:Cat Arya is chasing Episode 105.jpg|thumb|The cat Arya chases]]
[[Arya Stark]] explains to her father [[Eddard Stark|Eddard]] that she will be chasing cats as part of her [[Water Dance]] training. Her instructor [[Syrio Forel]] told her that every swordsman should study cats, because they are quiet, light on their feet, and quick.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Cripples, Bastards and Broken Things]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

The next day Arya chases a cat through the [[Red Keep]], attempting to gently catch it. The cat manages to evade her and runs down into the dungeons, causing Arya to stumble upon a secret conversation between [[Varys]] and [[Illyrio Mopatis]]. As she hides in a large [[Dragons|dragon]] skull, she overhears them say that &quot;the wolf and the lion&quot;, the Starks and Lannisters, will soon be fighting each other.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Wolf and the Lion]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 4]]===
Soon after King [[Joffrey Baratheon]] is assassinated, [[Margaery Tyrell]] visits his younger brother and heir apparent Prince [[Tommen Baratheon|Tommen]] in his bedchamber, hoping to befriend him before his mother Queen [[Cersei Lannister|Cersei]] can turn him against her. She finds him in bed, but Tommen is too young for Margaery's previous tactics of sexual seduction to be very useful. Tommen's cat [[Ser Pounce]] then jumps onto the bed, however, and she warms up to him by discussing his pet. She calls him a &quot;proper fellow&quot; but Tommen gets a concerned look and says that Joffrey did not like Ser Pounce very much: once he threatened to [[Flaying|skin the cat alive]], and then secretly mix its innards into Tommen's food, so he wouldn't know he was eating his own pet. In contrast to Joffrey's pervasive sadism, Tommen cares about his pet cat.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Oathkeeper]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
